    </node>
    <node id="topic:ground-truth-collection">
      <data key="d0">Topic</data>
      <data key="d1">Ground Truth Collection for Pseudonymization Evaluation</data>
      <data key="d2">0.95</data>
      <data key="d3">[{"quote": "we want to evaluate how they're doing with this pseudonymization ... we need to have annotations or like countries so they can compare what they predicted versus what it should actually be", "ts": 565, "source": "chapter_2"}, {"quote": "the starting to collect the ground truth, that's actually the most important one because it will take time for clinicians to do it, so the sooner that we have the stuff for them, the better.", "ts": 1990, "source": "Laura Gongas"}]</data>
      <data key="d4">["2", "4"]</data>
      <data key="d7">Steps: select cases (deceased patients, simple, low guidelines/handwriting), define entities with Brendan, get clinical team to annotate, optionally pre-populate with AI; need annotation tool meeting data privacy requirements; identified as highest-priority item</data>
    </node>
