      <data key="d28">["2", "4"]</data>
      <data key="d29">Ch2 claim that Cumulus has not settled on a pseudonymization approach reinforces the Ch4 decision to make ground truth collection the top priority (so evaluation can happen independently of Cumulus's choices)</data>
      <data key="d27">{"source_quote": {"quote": "I think they don't know what they're going to do, to be honest. ... he said he, John says he comes up with suggestions and then the data scientists suggest other stuff.", "ts": 955, "chapter": "2", "speaker": "Laura Gongas"}, "target_quote": {"quote": "the starting to collect the ground truth, that's actually the most important one because it will take time for clinicians to do it, so the sooner that we have the stuff for them, the better.", "ts": 1990, "chapter": "4", "speaker": "Laura Gongas"}}</data>
    </edge>
