      <data key="d26">0.9</data>
      <data key="d28">["2", "4"]</data>
      <data key="d29">Ch2 claim that without ground truth third-party vendors produce PoC work of unknown quality directly backs the Ch4 prioritisation of ground truth collection as the team's most important current item</data>
      <data key="d27">{"source_quote": {"quote": "if you don't give them ground truth, they'll just do like a kind of proof of concept thing that you don't even know if it works well or not. So you end up doing everything again.", "ts": 975, "chapter": "2", "speaker": "Laura Gongas"}, "target_quote": {"quote": "the starting to collect the ground truth, that's actually the most important one because it will take time for clinicians to do it, so the sooner that we have the stuff for them, the better.", "ts": 1990, "chapter": "4", "speaker": "Laura Gongas"}}</data>
